<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-11-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-11-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="599" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d599">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Marshall</persName> to
                                Colonel <persName type="to">Marshall S. Carter</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-11-25">25 November 1946</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1810. Urgent reference your 86251<note n="97" xml:id="d599fn97">
                                <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> inform all parties concerned
                            that it is my best judgement that immediate reduction of 10,000 to
                            remaining total of 5,000 is highly desirable and should be gotten
                            underway before some new incident creates impression of reduction under
                            hostile pressure. The numbers to be eliminated do little or no good and
                            really complicate the situation therefore I recommend prompt action.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>